course_metadata.title: Practical digital twins for smart housing and decarbonisation

content_chunks.content: Digital twins are in today's practice used at various context levels. It can be presented in many forms but commonly we do expect somewhat graphical representation that at least mimics the real construction entity throughout the chosen use case. Use cases are different and as such the information context that is needed, extends from one end to the other at different detail levels as well as with certain precision requirements. All that needs a well-planned level of information need activities. This course focuses onto level of information need developments that covers the use cases of smart housing and decarbonisation. This will be defined through structured information requirements that is attached onto digital model in where certain modelling workflows are explained.

Digital twins for smart housing, decarbonization workflows, and information management - this course delivers practical skills in developing digital twin solutions for sustainable building applications. Master information management in construction, implement level of information need development frameworks, and create information delivery manuals for structured data exchange. Learn construction classification systems, apply information structuring principles, and develop construction works structuring methodologies for BIM integration. Gain expertise in reference designation systems, implement construction classification international (CCI) standards, and utilize BIM modelling platforms for purposeful data exchange definitions. Develop data exchange workflows for smart housing applications and create decarbonization workflows through building information modeling data drops.
